---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Useful K Words for Scrabble — 5-Point Tile Strategy"
  description="Best K words for Scrabble ranked by score. K is worth 5 points and pairs perfectly with common tiles. Master KAYAK, KNACK, QUIRKY and more for consistent wins."
  keywords="useful K words scrabble, K words scrabble, best K scrabble words, K tile strategy, high scoring K words, 5 point tile scrabble, KN words scrabble, CK ending words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Useful K Words for Scrabble — 5-Point Tile Strategy",
    "description": "Best K words for Scrabble ranked by score. K is worth 5 points and pairs perfectly with common tiles.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-21",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/useful-k-words" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many points is K worth in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "K is worth 5 points in Scrabble with only 1 tile in the standard bag. At 5 points, it's a high-value tile that adds significant scoring punch to any word. K is the 5th highest-valued letter, behind Q (10), Z (10), X (8), and J (8)." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best short K words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The best short K words include KAY (10 pts), OAK (7 pts), INK (7 pts), YAK (10 pts), ELK (7 pts), ASK (7 pts), and SKI (7 pts). The 2-letter word KA (6 pts) is essential for parallel plays. K also forms the powerful -CK ending pattern seen in words like QUICK (20 pts), CHECK (16 pts), and KNOCK (15 pts)." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring K word in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Without premium squares, QUICKLY scores 25 points (7 letters), while QUIRKY scores 22 points in just 6 letters. For bingos, KAYAKING (20 + 50 = 70 pts) and KNOCKING (19 + 50 = 69 pts) are achievable with common tiles. Shorter high scorers include KAYAK (16 pts) and KNACK (15 pts)." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/letter-guides/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Letter Guides</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Useful K Words for Scrabble — 5-Point Tile Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-21">June 21, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        K is a premium tile hiding in plain sight. Worth 5 points with just 1 tile in the bag, it adds serious scoring power to common English words. Unlike J, Q, or Z that require specific supporting tiles, K works with everyday letters — BACK, KICK, THINK, WORK. It's the premium tile that never feels like a burden on your rack.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">K tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1 tile</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">25 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUICKLY (max)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">KA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">2-letter word (6 pts)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why K Is a Reliable Scorer</h2>

      <p>K appears in some of the most common English words — MAKE, TAKE, LIKE, WORK, BACK, THINK. This means when you draw K, you almost always have a playable word waiting. It doesn't require the specific tile combos that Q (needs U) or X (limited patterns) demand. K just works.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 K Efficiency</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">K averages <span class="text-white font-medium">2.0-2.5 points per tile</span> in the words it forms — higher than any common consonant (R, S, T, N all average ~1.2). Only premium tiles J, X, Z, and Q beat K's per-tile efficiency, but K is <span class="text-white font-medium">far easier to play</span> than any of them.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top K Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letters</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Pattern</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUICKLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">25</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">QU + CK + LY</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUIRKY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">22</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">QU + K + Y</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KAYAK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Double K</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KNACK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">KN + CK</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KNOCK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">KN + CK</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KAYAKING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">20</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Bingo (+50)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KIOSK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Double K (start+end)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BRISK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">-SK ending</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KAYAKED</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Bingo (+50)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">YAK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Quick 3-tile score</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Essential K Patterns</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">KN- (Silent K Start)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KNACK (15), KNOCK (15), KNIFE (12), KNEEL (9), KNIGHT (14), KNIT (8), KNOB (10), KNOW (11), KNOT (8) — the K is silent but still scores 5 points!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">-CK (Hard K Ending)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUICK (20), CHECK (16), THICK (14), BLACK (13), BRICK (13), CLICK (13), CLOCK (13), CRACK (13), STUCK (11), TRUCK (11)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Short K Words for Fast Plays</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">YAK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">KAY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">SKY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">SKI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">INK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">OAK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">ASK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">KA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">K Strategy Tips</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KA is your parallel play weapon:</span> KA (6 pts) is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. Use it for parallel plays — place K next to an existing letter to form KA downward while scoring the main word across. 6 points for 2 tiles is excellent efficiency.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target DLS/TLS for K:</span> K on a Double Letter Score = 10 points just for that tile. On Triple Letter Score = 15 points. Since K appears in short words (3-4 letters), positioning it on premium squares is often achievable. YAK with K on TLS = 20 points from 3 tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">K hooks well:</span> INK→INKS/INKY, ASK→ASKS/ASKED, OAK→OAKS/OAKEN. Many K words take S or ED extensions easily. Play the base word now and extend later — or hook onto existing board words by adding K to make new words.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't waste K in bingos unless scoring 70+:</span> K's 5 points are best used in short premium-square plays (15-25 pts for 3-5 tiles). In a bingo, K adds only 5 to the base — less impactful when you're already getting +50. Play K efficiently early, then chase bingos with remaining tiles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Cross-links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/words-starting-with-k/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Words Starting With K — all K openers ranked</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-kn/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Words Containing KN — silent K power plays</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/useful-c-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Useful C Words — Versatile 3-Point Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/useful-v-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Useful V Words — Tricky Consonant Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/useful-y-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Useful Y Words — Flexible Vowel-Consonant Plays</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all K words for your rack — free, instant, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
